I'm seeing these Cypress test failures across multiple runs: 13849 (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/13849/overview?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1), 13852 (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/13852/overview?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1), 13844 (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/13844/overview?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1)
• edit-existing-app.spec.ts
• aihub-results-table.spec.ts
• aihub-refinement-udf.spec.ts
• aihub-extraction.spec.ts
• aihub-data-types.spec.ts

these are failing because we merged frontend changes  (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/62441)that depend on backend changes (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/62345)

however, the backend changes have not been successfully deployed on crafting-cyp yet https://instabase.slack.com/archives/CCY413CSU/p1726247731343099

the infra team thinks this is a transient issue? https://instabase.slack.com/archives/CCY413CSU/p1726265122252739?thread_ts=1726264840.345779&cid=CCY413CSU

so hopefully the next deployment succeeds

if you’re stuck bc of these, please ask for a force merge!

i think this is easier than reverting since there’ll be 3 PRs to revert :disappointed: (frontend PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/62441), backend PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/62345), ibllm PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/62593))
